-- U.S. regulators put out banks' 'living wills' resolution plans
-- By Douwe Miedema
-- Wed Jul 02, 2014 04:40PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, July 2 (Reuters) - Two U.S. bank regulators on Wednesday published the public section of plans the largest banks need to submit to show how they can be safely unwound in times of financial crisis, known as "living wills."

